Also to clear a few things up:<br>
1) Christians do not beleive the world was created two thousands years ago with the birth of Jesus. Some say that it was 5000, however, this brings me to my next point.<br>
2) The original Hebrew for &quot;day&quot; in the book of Genesis (book in Torah which talks about creation) actually meant a day, a week, or a long period of time. This is open for HUGE speculation. I am a person of science, but also of faith. I've met many scientists that are Christian or Jewish. Einstein was a practicing Jew and he said once, &quot;Without science there is no religion. Without religion there is no science.&quot; This is a very good thought, when thought about. Also, one must ask himself especially in your case Tryunn, Why would God create creatures in the universe and then not give them any sign that he/she/it existed? Let me get one thing clear: I AM NOT TRYING TO CONVERT ANYONE. I'm merely explaining the reasons for why I beleive so people will stop thinking I'm an ignorant dumbass. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter>Vazaelle.com Community Center</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24>VCC Archives</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.vazaelle.com">Vazaelle.com</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard</a> Ver. 7.246j<br>Copyright 1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

